cian)|Maxwell]]\n| cover        = BlackSUMMERS'night (2016).jpg\n| alt          =\n| released     = {{Start date|2016|07|01}}\n| recorded     = 2015\u20132016\n| venue        =\n| studio       =\n| genre        = [[Soul music|Soul]], [[neo soul]]\n| length       = {{Duration|m=46|s=50}}\n| label        = [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| producer     = [[Maxwell (musician)|Musze]], Hod David, [[Stuart Matthewman]]\n| prev_title   = [[BLACKsummers'night|BLACK summers' night]]\n| prev_year    = 2009\n| next_title   =\n| next_year    =\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = blackSUMMERS'night\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Lake by the Ocean]]\n | single1date = April 8, 2016\n}}\n}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''blackSUMMERS'night''|noerror}}\n'''''blackSUMMERS'night''''' is the fifth [[studio album]] by American [[contemporary R&B|R&B]] singer and songwriter [[Maxwell (musician)|Maxwell]]. He produced most of the record with longtime collaborator and multi-instrumentalist Hod David; two songs were also co-produced by [[Stuart Matthewman]]. The album was released on July 1, 2016, by [[Columbia Records]] and charted at number three on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] while garnering widespread acclaim from critics.\n\n==Background==\n''blackSUMMERS'night'' was Maxwell's first record in seven years, following 2009's ''[[BLACKsummers'night]]'', which was the first in a planned trilogy of albums whose names were distinguished by the capitalization of letters in one phrase of the same title.<ref name=\"PM\">{{cite web|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/maxwell-blacksummersnight/|title=Maxwell: blackSUMMERS'night|last=Luecking|first=Eric|date=June 30, 2016|work=[[PopMatters]]|accessdate=July 7, 2016}}</ref> Maxwell told ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' in June 2016 that the trilogy is \"loosely based on the concept of a night out for a woman named Black Summers\". He produced most of ''blackSUMMERS'night'' with longtime collaborator Hod David.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2016/07/maxwell-releases-new-album-blacksummersnight|title=Maxwell Releases New Album \u2018blackSUMMERS\u2019night\u2019|last=Setaro|first=Shawn|date=July 1, 2016|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|accessdate=July 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Release and promotion ==\n''blackSUMMERS'night'' was released by [[Columbia Records]] on July 1, 2016.<ref name=\"PM\"/> In its first week of release, the album charted at number three on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and sold 59,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, 57,000 of which were entire copies of the record. It became the fourth album of Maxwell's career to reach the top 10 of the chart.<ref name=\"Caulfield\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7431229/blink-182-california-drake-views-no-1-on-billboard-200-albums-chart|title=Blink-182 Bumps Drake from No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=July 10, 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=July 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\nTo promote the album, \"[[Lake by the Ocean]]\" was released on April 8, 2016, as the [[lead single]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Maxwell Invites Fans to the 'Lake By the Ocean'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7326350/maxwell-lake-by-the-ocean|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last1=Mitchell|first1=Gail|date=May 8, 2016|accessdate=May 13, 2016|archivedate=2016 |archiveurl=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7326350/maxwell-lake-by-the-ocean|language=English}}</ref> On June 3, a [[lyric video]] for the song \"1990x\" was released.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hamm|first=Ken|date=June 3, 2016|url=http://www.soulbounce.com/2016/06/maxwell-releases-an-out-of-this-world-lyric-video-for-1990x/|title=Maxwell Releases An Out Of This World Lyric Video For \u20181990x\u2019|website=SoulBounce|accessdate=January 1, 2019}}</ref> Maxwell also toured the United States in support of the album, performing 29 concert dates from June to August.<ref>{{cite web|author=Zo|year=2016|url=https://www.okayplayer.com/news/maxwell-1990x-lyric-video.html|title=Maxwell Shares Airy, Delicate New Single '1990x'|website=[[Okayplayer]]|accessdate=January 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 7.3/10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/8129/Maxwell-blackSUMMERSnight.aspx |title=blackSUMMERS'night by Maxwell reviews |publisher=[[AnyDecentMusic?]] |accessdate=November 14, 2016}}</ref>\n| MC = 86/100<ref name=\"MC\"/>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/blacksummersnight-mw0002951022 |title=blackSUMMERS'night \u2013 Maxwell |last=Kellman |first=Andy |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=July 3, 2016}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Chicago Tribune]]''\n| rev2Score = {{Rating|3|4}}<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/kot/sc-ent-0701-maxwell-review-20160701-column.html |title=Maxwell remains a mysterious island unto himself on 'blackSUMMERS'night' |last=Kot |first=Greg |authorlink=Greg Kot |work=[[Chicago Tribune]] |date=July 1, 2016 |accessdate=July 7, 2016}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| rev3Score = A\u2212<ref name=\"EW\">{{cite journal |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/06/29/maxwells-blacksummersnight-ew-review |title=Maxwell's blackSUMMERS\u2019night: EW Review |last=Farber |first=Jim |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=June 29, 2016 |accessdate=July 4, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702011214/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/06/29/maxwells-blacksummersnight-ew-review |archivedate=July 2, 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Simpson\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/jun/30/maxwell-blacksummersnight-review-anguished-seductive-soul-man-returns |title=Maxwell: BlackSUMMERS\u2019night review \u2013 anguished, classy soul man returns |last=Simpson |first=Dave |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=June 30, 2016 |accessdate=July 3, 2016}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Irish Times]]''\n| rev5Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"irishtimes\"/>\n| rev6 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev6Score = 8.4/10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/22057-maxwell-blacksummersnight/ |title=Maxwell: blackSUMMERS'night |last=Haithcoat |first=Rebecca |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=July 12, 2016 |accessdate=July 14, 2016}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev7Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite journal |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/maxwell-blacksummersnight-20160701 |title=blackSUMMERS'night |last=Levy |first=Joe |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=July 1, 2016 |accessdate=July 3, 2016}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]''\n| rev8Score = 8/10<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.spin.com/2016/06/review-maxwell-blacksummersnight/ |title=Review: Maxwell Relieves That Stress (on His Syllables) With \u2018blackSUMMERS\u2019night\u2019 |last=Soto |first=Alfred |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |date=June 28, 2016 |accessdate=July 3, 2016}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]''\n| rev9Score = 9/10<ref>{{cite journal |title=Maxwell: blackSUMMERS'night |last=Anderson |first=Jason |work=[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]] |issue=232 |date=September 2016 |page=76}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[USA Today]]''\n| rev10Score = {{Rating|3.5|4}}<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2016/06/29/maxwell-looks-towards-light-blacksummersnight/86328792/ |title=Maxwell looks towards the light in 'blackSUMMERS'night' |last=Gardner |first=Elysa |work=[[USA Today]] |date=July 3, 2016 |accessdate=July 7, 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n''blackSUMMERS'night'' was met with widespread critical acclaim. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[Standard score|normalized]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream publications, the album received an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average]] score of 86, based on 15 reviews.<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/blacksummersnight-2016/maxwell |title=Reviews for blackSUMMERS'night (2016) by Maxwell |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=July 5, 2016}}</ref> \n\nReviewing the album in the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', [[Lorraine Ali]] found it charming and evocative while describing Maxwell as a \"transcendent\", multi-dimensional singer.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-et-ms-review-maxwell-20160701-snap-story.html|title=Maxwell's Long-Awaited 'blackSUMMERS'night' Flirts with Electronics and Jazz|last=Ali|first=Lorraine|authorlink=Lorraine Ali|date=July 1, 2016|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=July 7, 2016}}</ref> Jim Farber from ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' said the record \"exudes enough confidence to let his heart show and to let his music grow in any direction his muse demands\" while offering \"fresh textures to familiar soul sounds\".<ref name=\"EW\"/> In the opinion of ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s Joe Levy, \"the music evokes a tradition disappearing before our eyes \u2013 the spiritualized eroticism of [[Prince (musician)|Prince]], the jazzy soul extensions of [[Earth, Wind and Fire]] \u2013 without ever being of it.\"<ref name=\"RS\"/> In ''[[The Guardian]]'', Dave Simpson called it \"a classy comeback collection of anguished R&B\".<ref name=\"Simpson\"/>\n\nPaul Mardles was less enthusiastic in ''[[The Observer]]'', suggesting the record lacked memorable songs and innovative sounds; apart from funky songs such as \"Lake by the Ocean\", ''blackSUMMERS'night'' makes Maxwell, \"in the era of [[Frank Ocean]], look like the yesterday\u2019s man of R&B\", Madles wrote.<ref name=\"Mardles\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/jul/03/black-summers-night-maxwell-review|title=Maxwell: blackSummers\u2019 Night review \u2013 smooth 70s retro soul|last=Mardles|first=Paul|date=July 3, 2016|work=[[The Observer]]|accessdate=July 7, 2016}}</ref> [[Jim Carroll (journalist)|Jim Carroll]] of ''[[The Irish Times]]'' also found the music relatively \"old-fashioned\" and wrote, \"there are far too many moments here when he appears to be relying on that rich, chocolate voice to woo you rather than try something different or risky.\"<ref name=\"irishtimes\">{{cite news|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/culture/music/maxwell-black-summers-night-album-review-the-old-fashioned-soul-man-lays-it-on-thick-1.2737193|title=Maxwell \u2013 black SUMMERS\u2019 night album review: the old-fashioned soul man lays it on thick|last=Carroll|first=Jim|authorlink=Jim Carroll (journalist)|date=July 28, 2016|work=[[The Irish Times]]|accessdate=August 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n\n| title1 = All the Ways Love Can Feel\n| writer1 = [[Maxwell (musician)|Musze]], Hod David, Travis Sayles\n| extra1 = David, Musze\n| length1 = 5:21\n\n| title2 = The Fall\n| writer2 = Musze, David, Sayles, Shedrick Mitchell\n| extra2 = David, Musze\n| length2 = 4:11\n\n| title3 = III\n| writer3 = Musze, David\n| extra3 = David, Musze\n| length3 = 4:47\n\n| title4 = [[Lake by the Ocean]]\n| writer4 = Musze, David\n| extra4 = David, Musze\n| length4 = 3:59\n\n| title5 = Fingers Crossed\n| writer5 = Musze, David\n| extra5 = David, Musze\n| length5 = 4:38\n\n| title6 = Hostage\n| writer6 = Musze, David\n| extra6 = David, Musze\n| length6 = 3:55\n\n| title7 = 1990x\n| writer7 = Musze, David\n| extra7 = David, Musze\n| length7 = 4:44\n\n| title8 = Gods\n| writer8 = Musze, David\n| extra8 = David, Musze\n| length8 = 3:35\n\n| title9 = Lost\n| writer9 = Musze, [[Stuart Matthewman]]\n| extra9 = Matthewman, Musze\n| length9 = 3:57\n\n| title10 = Of All Kind\n| writer10 = Musze, David\n| extra10 = David, Musze\n| length10 = 3:42\n\n| title11 = Listen Hear\n| writer11 = Musze, Matthewman\n| extra11 = Matthewman, Musze\n| length11 = 3:38\n\n| title12 = Night\n| writer12 = Earth\n| extra12 = \n| length12 = 0:23\n}}\n\